  "doc_id": "5153",
  "text": "The present cross-sectional study was embedded in the 'Be active, eat right' study, which aims to assess the effects of an overweight prevention protocol, as described in detail elsewhere [CITATION_1] . The Medical Ethics Committee of Erasmus MC University Medical Centre Rotterdam approved the study protocol. A total of 13 638 parents of 5-yearolds were invited by mail for a well-child visit (which has an attendance rate of 95%) [CITATION_2] at one of the nine municipal health services across the Netherlands participating in the study. These parents were also invited to participate in the 'Be active, eat right' study, 64.4% of whom provided written informed consent. Baseline data were collected during the 2007-2008 school year, and these data were used for the present study. Parents completed a questionnaire with items on demographic, socioeconomic, and lifestyle-related characteristics of themselves and their child. Height and weight of the children were measured by trained health care professionals during well-child visits.",
